  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Arcoiris Liberation Team</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) provides accompaniment of LGBTQ migrants in detention, including moral and material support for legal cases
2) campaigns to uplift the stories of individual LGBTQ migrants in detention, in order to publicly pressure ICE to release them
3) highlights, through individual and larger campaigns, the injustice of immigration detention and the particular abuses faced by detained LGBTQ migrants
4) develop leaders within the detained LGBTQ migrant community.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Trans Queer Migrant Defense Project builds power in the LGBTQ migrant community to defend itself against criminalization, detention and deportation by creating community-based alternatives and changing the immigration conversation in Arizona. The grant will allow Arcoiris to hire a stipended coordinator from the affected community to coordinate detention visits, monitor detention conditions, and organize previously detained LGBTQ migrants.</narrative>
  </description>
